[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":569},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F11\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F11\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F11\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F11\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01\u002F":544,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F11\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01\u002F":553},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20190511\u002F638155277\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":529,"date":530,"description":531,"extension":532,"lang":533,"meta":534,"navigation":82,"path":535,"readingMinutes":536,"seo":537,"standalone":538,"stem":539,"tags":540,"tldr":541,"updated":530,"url":542,"__hash__":543},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-closures-basics-01.md","What's a Closure in JavaScript? A Beginner-Friendly Walkthrough","1001393747",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":523},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,34,37,175,182,350,356,464,473,486,490,493,496,505,512,519],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"There's this concept in JavaScript called a closure, and you hear people say the word all the time — closure this, closure that. I did a bit of reading on it, so I'm jotting down some notes here.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"closure","Closure",[17,25,26],{},"First off, the MDN docs have a short explanation: \"A closure is the combination of a function and the lexical environment within which that function was declared.\" That's a bit wordy and hard to parse though. After reading around and digesting it myself, my own version is: a closure is a function declared inside another function.",[17,28,29],{},"So what do I mean by \"a function inside a function\"?",[12,31,33],{"id":32},"an-example","An example",[17,35,36],{},"The closure concept is mostly tied to variable scope, so let me write out an example to walk through it.",[38,39,44],"pre",{"className":40,"code":41,"language":42,"meta":43,"style":43},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u002F\u002F icash starts with a balance of 1000 $\nvar icash = 1000;\n\nfunction count(price) {\n return icash = icash - price;\n\n}\n\ncount(50);\ncount(50);\nconsole.log(icash);\n","js","",[45,46,47,56,77,84,104,122,127,133,138,152,163],"code",{"__ignoreMap":43},[48,49,52],"span",{"class":50,"line":51},"line",1,[48,53,55],{"class":54},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F icash starts with a balance of 1000 $\n",[48,57,59,63,67,70,74],{"class":50,"line":58},2,[48,60,62],{"class":61},"sWyjQ","var",[48,64,66],{"class":65},"sMAXC"," icash ",[48,68,69],{"class":61},"=",[48,71,73],{"class":72},"sCcAr"," 1000",[48,75,76],{"class":65},";\n",[48,78,80],{"class":50,"line":79},3,[48,81,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},true,"\n",[48,85,87,90,94,97,101],{"class":50,"line":86},4,[48,88,89],{"class":61},"function",[48,91,93],{"class":92},"sj_SG"," count",[48,95,96],{"class":65},"(",[48,98,100],{"class":99},"s_sBn","price",[48,102,103],{"class":65},") {\n",[48,105,107,110,112,114,116,119],{"class":50,"line":106},5,[48,108,109],{"class":61}," return",[48,111,66],{"class":65},[48,113,69],{"class":61},[48,115,66],{"class":65},[48,117,118],{"class":61},"-",[48,120,121],{"class":65}," price;\n",[48,123,125],{"class":50,"line":124},6,[48,126,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,128,130],{"class":50,"line":129},7,[48,131,132],{"class":65},"}\n",[48,134,136],{"class":50,"line":135},8,[48,137,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,139,141,144,146,149],{"class":50,"line":140},9,[48,142,143],{"class":92},"count",[48,145,96],{"class":65},[48,147,148],{"class":72},"50",[48,150,151],{"class":65},");\n",[48,153,155,157,159,161],{"class":50,"line":154},10,[48,156,143],{"class":92},[48,158,96],{"class":65},[48,160,148],{"class":72},[48,162,151],{"class":65},[48,164,166,169,172],{"class":50,"line":165},11,[48,167,168],{"class":65},"console.",[48,170,171],{"class":92},"log",[48,173,174],{"class":65},"(icash);\n",[17,176,177,178,181],{},"Now imagine a bunch more code comes after that, and somewhere down the line I call the ",[45,179,180],{},"icash"," variable again. This time I want each person's starting balance to be 1000 + 200.",[38,183,185],{"className":40,"code":184,"language":42,"meta":43,"style":43},"\u002F\u002F icash starts with a balance of 1000 $\nvar icash = 1000;\n\nfunction count(price) {\n return icash = icash - price;\n\n}\n\ncount(50);\ncount(50);\nconsole.log(icash);\n\n\nfunction countAdd(price) {\n return icash = icash + price;\n\n}\n\ncountAdd(200);\nconsole.log(icash);\n",[45,186,187,191,203,207,219,233,237,241,245,255,265,273,278,283,297,313,318,323,328,341],{"__ignoreMap":43},[48,188,189],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,190,55],{"class":54},[48,192,193,195,197,199,201],{"class":50,"line":58},[48,194,62],{"class":61},[48,196,66],{"class":65},[48,198,69],{"class":61},[48,200,73],{"class":72},[48,202,76],{"class":65},[48,204,205],{"class":50,"line":79},[48,206,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,208,209,211,213,215,217],{"class":50,"line":86},[48,210,89],{"class":61},[48,212,93],{"class":92},[48,214,96],{"class":65},[48,216,100],{"class":99},[48,218,103],{"class":65},[48,220,221,223,225,227,229,231],{"class":50,"line":106},[48,222,109],{"class":61},[48,224,66],{"class":65},[48,226,69],{"class":61},[48,228,66],{"class":65},[48,230,118],{"class":61},[48,232,121],{"class":65},[48,234,235],{"class":50,"line":124},[48,236,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,238,239],{"class":50,"line":129},[48,240,132],{"class":65},[48,242,243],{"class":50,"line":135},[48,244,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,246,247,249,251,253],{"class":50,"line":140},[48,248,143],{"class":92},[48,250,96],{"class":65},[48,252,148],{"class":72},[48,254,151],{"class":65},[48,256,257,259,261,263],{"class":50,"line":154},[48,258,143],{"class":92},[48,260,96],{"class":65},[48,262,148],{"class":72},[48,264,151],{"class":65},[48,266,267,269,271],{"class":50,"line":165},[48,268,168],{"class":65},[48,270,171],{"class":92},[48,272,174],{"class":65},[48,274,276],{"class":50,"line":275},12,[48,277,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,279,281],{"class":50,"line":280},13,[48,282,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,284,286,288,291,293,295],{"class":50,"line":285},14,[48,287,89],{"class":61},[48,289,290],{"class":92}," countAdd",[48,292,96],{"class":65},[48,294,100],{"class":99},[48,296,103],{"class":65},[48,298,300,302,304,306,308,311],{"class":50,"line":299},15,[48,301,109],{"class":61},[48,303,66],{"class":65},[48,305,69],{"class":61},[48,307,66],{"class":65},[48,309,310],{"class":61},"+",[48,312,121],{"class":65},[48,314,316],{"class":50,"line":315},16,[48,317,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,319,321],{"class":50,"line":320},17,[48,322,132],{"class":65},[48,324,326],{"class":50,"line":325},18,[48,327,83],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":82},[48,329,331,334,336,339],{"class":50,"line":330},19,[48,332,333],{"class":92},"countAdd",[48,335,96],{"class":65},[48,337,338],{"class":72},"200",[48,340,151],{"class":65},[48,342,344,346,348],{"class":50,"line":343},20,[48,345,168],{"class":65},[48,347,171],{"class":92},[48,349,174],{"class":65},[17,351,352,353,355],{},"And here you'll notice ",[45,354,180],{}," somehow ends up as 1100 $. That's down to scope pollution. So how do we write this with a closure instead?",[38,357,359],{"className":40,"code":358,"language":42,"meta":43,"style":43},"function count() {\n var icash = 1000;\n return function (price){\n  icash = icash - price;\n  return icash;\n }\n}\nvar item = count();\nitem(100);\nitem(200);\n",[45,360,361,370,383,398,411,419,424,428,442,454],{"__ignoreMap":43},[48,362,363,365,367],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,364,89],{"class":61},[48,366,93],{"class":92},[48,368,369],{"class":65},"() {\n",[48,371,372,375,377,379,381],{"class":50,"line":58},[48,373,374],{"class":61}," var",[48,376,66],{"class":65},[48,378,69],{"class":61},[48,380,73],{"class":72},[48,382,76],{"class":65},[48,384,385,387,390,393,395],{"class":50,"line":79},[48,386,109],{"class":61},[48,388,389],{"class":61}," function",[48,391,392],{"class":65}," (",[48,394,100],{"class":99},[48,396,397],{"class":65},"){\n",[48,399,400,403,405,407,409],{"class":50,"line":86},[48,401,402],{"class":65},"  icash ",[48,404,69],{"class":61},[48,406,66],{"class":65},[48,408,118],{"class":61},[48,410,121],{"class":65},[48,412,413,416],{"class":50,"line":106},[48,414,415],{"class":61},"  return",[48,417,418],{"class":65}," icash;\n",[48,420,421],{"class":50,"line":124},[48,422,423],{"class":65}," }\n",[48,425,426],{"class":50,"line":129},[48,427,132],{"class":65},[48,429,430,432,435,437,439],{"class":50,"line":135},[48,431,62],{"class":61},[48,433,434],{"class":65}," item ",[48,436,69],{"class":61},[48,438,93],{"class":92},[48,440,441],{"class":65},"();\n",[48,443,444,447,449,452],{"class":50,"line":140},[48,445,446],{"class":92},"item",[48,448,96],{"class":65},[48,450,451],{"class":72},"100",[48,453,151],{"class":65},[48,455,456,458,460,462],{"class":50,"line":154},[48,457,446],{"class":92},[48,459,96],{"class":65},[48,461,338],{"class":72},[48,463,151],{"class":65},[17,465,466,467,469,470,472],{},"You can see the ",[45,468,180],{}," balance goes down, and each time you run it, only the inner function runs and only the inner ",[45,471,180],{}," variable gets updated.",[17,474,475,476,478,479,482,483,485],{},"One thing to watch out for here: since ",[45,477,446],{}," points to ",[45,480,481],{},"count()",", you can keep calling this method over and over, and the inner memory (",[45,484,180],{},") never gets released — so you can keep using it.",[12,487,489],{"id":488},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,491,492],{},"That's basically the core idea of closures, though I'll admit this writeup isn't super detailed.",[17,494,495],{},"Reference articles:",[17,497,498],{},[499,500,504],"a",{"href":501,"rel":502},"https:\u002F\u002Fwcc723.github.io\u002Fjavasc